One thing about Dr. Ray Peat I admire is how he used to take EVERYONE seriously. He'd listen as attentively to like a house cleaning lady talking about old wives remedies as to uni biochemistry professors. He would sincerely ask 5 year old children about their political opinions.

He even had that one anecdote where while he was watering his garden a few blue jays were chirping at him and he figured out they wanted him to point the hose at them, but were scared of the water spray, so he switched to a gentler nozzle and they proceeded to play in the spray
Just an attempt to communicate with any single living being that is willing to engage in some way with you, always in a serious and meaningful way
